  "message": "chore: untrack conformance _scratch dirs and legacy python submodule\n\nThese paths were tracked as gitlinks (nested git repos auto-detected\nas submodules) despite matching existing .gitignore patterns, causing\npersistent dirty-tree noise from untracked content inside them:\n\n- crates/mcp-agent-mail-conformance/.../python_reference/_scratch/\n  (9 conformance test run dirs with archive gitlinks + db.sqlite3)\n- legacy_python_mcp_agent_mail_code/mcp_agent_mail\n  (legacy Python reference code, submodule gitlink)\n\nRemoving from the index so the existing .gitignore patterns take\neffect. All files remain on disk unchanged.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
